        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 10 at 7:11PM MDT by NWS North Platte NE</headline>
        <description>At 710 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Grant, moving north at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Grant, Madrid, and Wild Horse Spring.

This includes Highway 61 between mile markers 55 and 74.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

To report severe weather, contact your nearest law enforcement
agency. They will relay your report to the National Weather Service
office in North Platte.</instruction>
